83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
B-Engrossed
House Bill 4036
Ordered by the House March 3
Including House Amendments dated February 12 and March 3
Introduced and printed pursuant to House Rule 12.00. Presession filed (at the request of House Interim Committee
on Housing and Homelessness for Representative Pam Marsh)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability standards.
Digest: This Act sets up a bond fund to preserve low-cost housing and requires OHCS to report
on low-cost housing barriers. (Flesch Readability Score: 63.8).
Establishes the Housing Opportunity, Longevity and Durability Fund to deposit Article XI-Q
bonds to be used by the Housing and Community Services Department to preserve affordable hous-
ing at risk of loss. [Authorizes the State Treasurer to issue $100 million in bonds for the fund for the
2025-2027 biennium.]
Requires the department to, with input from stakeholders, report to the interim committees of
the Legislative Assembly relating to housing on or before December 1, 2026, on legal and policy
barriers to affordable housing production.
Declares an emergency, effective on passage.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to affordable housing; creating new provisions; amending ORS 456.559 and 456.824; and
3 declaring an emergency.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part of ORS 456.766 to
6 456.828.
7 SECTION 2. (1) The Housing Opportunity, Longevity and Durability Fund is established
8 in the State Treasury, separate and distinct from the General Fund. Interest earned on
9 moneys in the Housing Opportunity, Longevity and Durability Fund shall be credited to the
10 fund.
11 (2) The fund consists of moneys deposited into the fund from bonds issued by the State
12 Treasurer pursuant to ORS 286A.035 for the Housing and Community Services Department
13 to be used for affordable housing preservation.
14 (3) Moneys in the fund are continuously appropriated to the department to:
15 (a) Acquire, construct, remodel, repair, equip or furnish affordable housing at risk of
16 loss, as described in ORS 456.824 (2), that is or will be owned or operated, as those terms are
17 defined in ORS 458.480, by the State of Oregon for the purpose of providing affordable hous-
18 ing;
19 (b) Pay the costs incurred by the department to administer the fund; and
20 (c) Pay bond-related costs, as defined in ORS 286A.816.
21 SECTION 3. On or before December 1, 2026, the Housing and Community Services De-
22 partment shall submit a report in the manner provided by ORS 192.245 to the interim com-
23 mittees of the Legislative Assembly related to housing that incorporates feedback from key
