1 stakeholders, including affordable housing providers, finance entities and tenant advocates,
2 and that:
3 (1) Evaluates the impact of and offers improvements to any state laws or practices, pol-
4 icies or rules of the department that negatively impact the efficiency, effectiveness and cost
5 of operating affordable housing, including impacts to leasing, screening applicants, filling
6 vacancies, maintaining tenant wait lists, recertifying tenants, conducting inspections, col-
7 lecting rent, managing property and complying with regulations; and
8 (2) Evaluates opportunities to streamline, reduce or eliminate reporting requirements of
9 affordable housing providers for state and federal programs and funding sources that are
10 administered by the department.
11 SECTION 4. ORS 456.824 is amended to read:
12 456.824. The Housing and Community Services Department shall establish and maintain an af-
13 fordable housing preservation program to coordinate affordable housing preservation efforts and
14 incentivize the analysis and preservation of affordable housing, including publicly supported housing
15 and manufactured dwelling parks. Under the program, the department shall:
16 (1) Collect and maintain data from local, state and federal sources on affordable housing in this
17 state, including the status of existing affordability restrictions and rental assistance contracts at
18 publicly supported housing.
19 (2) Identify categories of affordable housing at risk of loss, including:
20 (a) Properties with expiring federal rent assistance contracts;
21 (b) Properties with expiring affordability restrictions;
22 (c) Properties with affordability restrictions in [physical or financial distress] financial or
23 physical distress, including physical distress that requires rehabilitation, repair or replace-
24 ment of such building systems, components or materials that have exceeded, or within a
25 reasonable period will exceed, their effective useful lives; and
26 (d) Manufactured dwelling parks at risk of sale or closure.
27 (3) Take actions to promote housing stability, for residents of:
28 (a) Affordable housing that is at risk of loss or that has been recently lost; or
29 (b) Residents of manufactured dwelling parks or marinas at risk of sale or closure.
30 (4) Establish and periodically update evaluation criteria for affordable housing preservation [in-
31 vestments].
32 (5) Identify and aggregate available sources of funding, including moneys available from federal
33 and private grants or programs, appropriations by the Legislative Assembly, existing funds of the
34 department or financing available from Article XI-Q bond proceeds under ORS 286A.824 or 458.480
35 to 458.490 or section 2 of this 2026 Act or proceeds of other bonds issued by the State Treasurer,
36 and use such sources of funding to implement preservation [investments for] of affordable housing in
37 accordance with the established evaluation criteria.
38 (6) Regularly analyze operating expenses of the existing portfolio of publicly supported housing
39 that is funded by the department to inform the department’s underwriting standards for financing
40 the construction of new and the preservation of existing publicly supported housing and to inform
41 forecasts of preservation funding needs.
42 (7) Regularly update and publish an affordable housing preservation strategy framework report
43 that includes information identified in subsections (1) and (2) of this section and forecasts the fi-
44 nancial need to preserve affordable housing.
45 (8) Execute the duties of the department under ORS 456.766 to 456.828.
